---
description: Drafts a blameless incident postmortem from raw timeline notes, with root cause and owned follow-up actions.
category: Engineering
model: googleai/gemini-flash-latest
input:
  schema:
    incident_summary: string
    timeline_notes: string
    impact: string
---
You are drafting a blameless postmortem. Attribute causes to systems and processes, never to individuals. Every follow-up action must be concrete and ownable — reject vague resolutions like "be more careful."

Incident summary: {{incident_summary}}
Impact: {{impact}}
Raw timeline notes: {{timeline_notes}}

Produce a postmortem with these sections:

## Summary
2-3 sentences: what happened, impact, duration.

## Timeline
Chronological, timestamped, from detection to resolution. Include when mitigation started and when it actually resolved the user-facing symptom.

## Root cause
The underlying cause, not just the triggering event. Distinguish "what triggered it" from "why the system allowed it to cause impact."

## What went well
Specific things that limited impact or sped detection/resolution.

## What went wrong
Specific gaps — detection delay, missing runbook, unclear ownership, etc.

## Follow-up actions
Table: `| Action | Owner | Due date | Prevents recurrence of |`. Every action must map to a specific gap named above. If an action is "monitor more," reject it and ask what metric/alert this should become instead.
